    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nNeovim crashed when trying to open a float window on a diagnostic that has `vim.NIL` in `relatedInformation`.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Install `nimlangserver`\n2. Open float window on a diagnostic in a `nim` source file\n3. Notice that on `textDocument/publishDiagnostics`, `relatedInformation` is `vim.NIL` in `TRACE` log level\n4. Boom an error pops out\n\n```\nE5108: Lua: /usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/diagnostic/_float.lua:216: bad argument #1 to 'ipairs' (table expected, got userdata)\nstack traceback:\n\t[C]: in function 'ipairs'\n\t/usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/diagnostic/_float.lua:216: in function 'open_float'\n\tvim/_core/defaults.lua: in function <vim/_core/defaults.lua:0>\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe floating window should open as usual.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.13.0-dev-205+g0e07b2a1e2\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty with tmux\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nAUR",
